    "In detecting fake news, three approaches are commonly used by researchers: knowledge-based (fact-checking), content approaches, and context approaches [38] [12].",
    "This section will describe each feature in more detail for better understanding.",
    "Fig. 1 summarizes these features.",
    "A. Knowledge-based ApproachesThis approach works by attempting to discover whether there are facts that support the claim made in a news item [39].",
